Pegasystems Inc. is a software company that provides Business Process Management (BPM) solutions. Founded in 1983, Pegasystems deals with rules-based BPM technology. The company previously acquired Chordiant Software in 2010, Antenna Software in 2013, Profeatable Corporation in 2014, and OpenSpan in… MorePegasystems Inc. is a software company that provides Business Process Management (BPM) solutions. Founded in 1983, Pegasystems deals with rules-based BPM technology. The company previously acquired Chordiant Software in 2010, Antenna Software in 2013, Profeatable Corporation in 2014, and OpenSpan in 2016.
• The company completed its acquisition of Profeatable Corporation in mid-2014.

2013 and Earlier:
 IT Priorities:
• Pegasystems acquired Antenna Software in October, 2013, and operates Antenna as an independent business unit.
· Company has opened a new network operations center
· Expanding cloud… More• The company completed its acquisition of Profeatable Corporation in mid-2014.

2013 and Earlier:
 IT Priorities:
• Pegasystems acquired Antenna Software in October, 2013, and operates Antenna as an independent business unit.
· Company has opened a new network operations center
· Expanding cloud infrastructure globally

IT Structure:
· IT department is head quartered in Cambridge, MA
IT department is primarily responsible for supporting the software development operations, in additional the company's global infrastructure.
· The applications group is devoted toward web development of the company's CRM and workflow platforms. Most of these applications are developed through Java and .NET. Given that Pega provides technology applications for its customers, the company uilized its own products for these areas to the greatest extent possible. 
· The infrastructure group is responsible for handling the information security, data center, and telecommunications. The company network uses Cisco routers and switches and IBM servers that are virtualized with VMware and run on Windows Server 2008. The company's data storage is backed up using EMC Networker.
· The budget is typically finalized in Q1.

IT Intelligence Snippet:
2013:
· Less than 30% of IT staff is dedicated to the sustenance of its ERP platform, and less than 30% of
· ERP support is outsourced to a third party. 
· Expects around 120 releases/updates a year with its current ERP solution.





